# Hub contributing (template skeleton only)

When **`session.json`** has `"mode": "hub"`, also follow [CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md):

- Keep examples generic (`my-app`, `my-agent`) — no real project or domain names
- Scope: session binding, repos registry, worktrees, hooks, docs, install — not domain features
- Before opening a hub PR, run:

```bash
python3 scripts/test_session_binding.py
python3 scripts/test_git_remotes.py
python3 scripts/test_hub_upgrade.py
```

- Open from a feature branch; wait for CI (`test` workflow)
- **Do not** use `gh pr merge --auto` or merge unless the maintainer explicitly asks
